The underdevelopment Berton development project in Dubai, UAE, is 64.9% complete according to Azizi Developments, a leading real estate and lifestyle developer. The developer explained that the residential building’s blockwork and structure have been fully completed while the internal plastering works are 99% complete. All the elevator works are 96% complete with the second phase of the mechanical, electrical, and plumbing (MEP) having reached 51% completion. Facade works have reached 85% while tiling works have reached 90%. The CEO of Azizi Developments, Fahad Azizi, stated that joining forces with several hardworking parties and an extraordinary contractor have contributed to the project’s progress. He noted that the unique way of life the project embodies reflects the company’s vision of urbanism. The developer aims to deliver the Berton Development Project by the third quarter of 2022. The Berton development project features 41 bedroom apartments, 190 studio units, and 14 two-bedroom apartments alongside 16 penthouses. The project is also said to blend interior artistry with masterful craftsmanship with gracefully furnished homes that are accompanied by state-of-the-art décor, generous space, and high-end parquet flooring. Also Read: Refurbishment of Al Thuraya Tower 1 Property in Dubai, UAE, Complete The CEO of Azizi Developments happily expressed that the property offers the opportunity to live in one of the most prominent up-and-coming locations in the country, to customers. With its proximity to the Sheikh Zayed Road, the EXPO 2020 Route metro line as well as the Sheikh Mohammed Bin Zayed Road, Berton is well-connected to the entirety of Dubai’s pivotal points of interest. Farhad concluded by stating that they look forward to completing the world-class development as it will profoundly enrich the lives of those that will live in the residence.